## Week 1 — 25th May to 2nd June

### Goals
- Establish ROS connection to LoCoBot
- Validate basic arm control via Interbotix SDK

### Completed
- Fixed ROS network configuration (ROS_IP mismatch between 35.12.212.139 and 35.12.212.57)
- Identified correct SDK class: `InterbotixLocobotXS` with `arm_model='wx250s'` required
- Confirmed `bot.arm.go_to_home_pose()` and `bot.arm.go_to_sleep_pose()` working
- Confirmed `set_ee_pose_components()` and `set_ee_cartesian_trajectory()` working

### Issues Encountered
- `wrist_rotate` motor had hardware error flag (red flashing LED) — fixed by reboot via SDK
- `load_configs:=true` caused EEPROM write failure on elbow motor — fixed with `load_configs:=false`
- `roll` parameter in `set_ee_pose_components` had no effect at `pitch=π/2` due to gimbal lock singularity
- `forearm_roll` direct joint control identified as correct approach for tilt correction
- Phase 2 height correction unstable due to: sensor hand-held, pitch drift during corrections, motor vibration corrupting readings

### Hardware Event
- Arm over-extended during testing, lifted base, home position shifted
- 20V adapter removed while powered — spark occurred on connector
- All Dynamixel motors lost power — confirmed as hardware fault
- Direct SDK ping at all baudrates returned no response on all motor IDs
- Camera and computer unaffected (separate 12V circuit)
- Technician inspection scheduled June 9th

### Next Steps
- Resolve hardware power fault
- Mount HC-SR04 rigidly to gripper
- Test improved Phase 2 architecture on hardware
- Write and test TOF Arduino code
- Record all Phase 1 videos for documentation

